HEADWORD: Epaule
<hw>E*paule"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧paule</ets> shoulder, shoulder of a bastion. See
<er>Epaulet</er>, and cf. <er>Spall</er> the shoulder.]</ety>
<fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>The shoulder of a bastion, or the place where
its face and flank meet and form the angle, called the angle of the
shoulder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epaulement</ent>⟦br⟧
